    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you're ok with depending on a running docker container, and want something well-supported, you could consider using <a href=\"https://github.com/localstack/localstack\" rel=\"noreferrer\">localstack</a></p>\n\n<p>Before running your tests, start S3 like so:</p>\n\n<pre><code>docker run --name localstack -d -p 5000:5000 -e SERVICES=s3:5000 localstack/localstack\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>And then stop it when tests complete like so:</p>\n\n<pre><code>docker stop localstack\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>You'll need to configure your S3 client to point to localhost:5000 for tests.  In Java, this can be done like so:</p>\n\n<pre><code>        AmazonS3ClientBuilder.standard()\n            .withEndpointConfiguration(new AwsClientBuilder.EndpointConfiguration(\n                 \"http://localhost:5000\", \n                 \"us-west-2\"))\n            .build();\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 8660948,
      "reputation" : 1420,
      "user_id" : 6483409,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/2310b74a51fb9ffb03b51495d27095c0?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "robothy",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6483409/robothy"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1668070745,
    "creation_date" : 1668070745,
    "answer_id" : 74386397,
    "question_id" : 6615988,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Robothy/local-s3\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">LocalS3</a> is a good choice.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><p>It's based on Netty and without heavy other dependencies. Startup a LocalS3 service or <a href=\"https://hub.docker.com/r/luofuxiang/local-s3\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Docker container</a> is super quick.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Support commonly used AmazonS3 APIs. Include versioned objects, multipart uploads, etc.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Support in-memory and persistence mode.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1645396,
      "reputation" : 206,
      "user_id" : 1517027,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/se0mT.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "johannesboyne",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1517027/johannesboyne"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1714546109,
    "creation_date" : 1714546109,
    "answer_id" : 78412387,
    "question_id" : 6615988,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><em>(maintainer here)</em></p>\n<p>There is also <a href=\"https://github.com/johannesboyne/gofakes3\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">(Gofake)S3</a>!</p>\n<p>This tool can be used to run a test server, for example, to support testing AWS Lambda functions that interact with S3. It also serves as a straightforward and convenient S3 mock and test server for various development needs.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5395380,
      "reputation" : 1656,
      "user_id" : 17547033,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3a3672aa0c64568638e19db88d9f87d7?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "nik0x1",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/17547033/nik0x1"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1714676430,
    "creation_date" : 1714676430,
    "answer_id" : 78421224,
    "question_id" : 6615988,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>For your purposes you can use Testcontainers + LocalStack Module.</p>\n<p>The approach is roughly the following:</p>\n<p>Add the dependency (example for <code>pom.xml</code>):</p>\n<pre><code>&lt;dependency&gt;\n   &lt;groupId&gt;org.testcontainers&lt;/groupId&gt;\n   &lt;artifactId&gt;junit-jupiter&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n   &lt;version&gt;1.19.7&lt;/version&gt;\n   &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;\n&lt;/dependency&gt;\n&lt;dependency&gt;\n   &lt;groupId&gt;org.testcontainers&lt;/groupId&gt;\n   &lt;artifactId&gt;localstack&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n   &lt;version&gt;1.19.7&lt;/version&gt;\n   &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;\n&lt;/dependency&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Create a test class (example for JUnit 5):</p>\n<pre><code>@Testcontainers\nclass MyClassTest {\n\n    @Container\n    private static final LocalStackContainer localstack =\n            new LocalStackContainer(\n                    DockerImageName.parse(&quot;localstack/localstack:0.11.3&quot;)\n            ).withServices(S3);\n\n    @Test\n    void check() {\n        // AWS SDK v2\n        S3Client s3 = S3Client\n                .builder()\n                .endpointOverride(localstack.getEndpoint())\n                .credentialsProvider(\n                        StaticCredentialsProvider.create(\n                                AwsBasicCredentials.create(localstack.getAccessKey(), localstack.getSecretKey())\n                        )\n                )\n                .region(Region.of(localstack.getRegion()))\n                .build();\n\n        // some actions and assertions\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Note:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://java.testcontainers.org/modules/localstack/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">LocalStack Module</a> (have example for AWS SDK v1 and Gradle)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://java.testcontainers.org/test_framework_integration/junit_4/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Testcontainers with JUnit 4</a></li>\n</ol>\n"
  } ],
