  "title" : "How to mock Amazon S3 in an integration test",
  "body" : "<p>I'm trying to get an \"walking skeleton\" of my app up that will use S3 for persistence. I would like to use a fake S3 service so each developer's desktop can read/write at will.</p>\n\n<p>I thought <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/mocks3/\" rel=\"noreferrer\">mocks3</a> would be perfect, as I could get a jetty server up in my jUnit tests. The problem is that mocks3 doesn't allow any <em>writes</em>. Not even to set it up as far as I can tell.</p>\n\n<p>So how do others do this?</p>\n"
}